            "comments": [
                {
                    "file": "designs/cxl-cci-over-mctp.md",
                    "line": 58,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Patrick Williams",
                        "email": "patrick@stwcx.xyz",
                        "username": "williamspatrick"
                    },
                    "message": "We need more contents here (or in the design).  What specifically is this daemon going to do?  What existing dbus objects is it expecting to interact with?  What dbus interfaces need to be hosted by this daemon?  What new dbus interfaces are going to be proposed to facilitate this requirement?"
                },
                {
                    "file": "designs/cxl-cci-over-mctp.md",
                    "line": 75,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Patrick Williams",
                        "email": "patrick@stwcx.xyz",
                        "username": "williamspatrick"
                    },
                    "message": "Could be?  Or will be?  This is where you're defining the design.  You shouldn't have unanswered because it directly impacts your implementation."
                },
                {
                    "file": "designs/cxl-cci-over-mctp.md",
                    "line": 79,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Patrick Williams",
                        "email": "patrick@stwcx.xyz",
                        "username": "williamspatrick"
                    },
                    "message": "Do these need to be \"libraries\"?  I don't think we have any need for that.  We should structure this like pldmd, right?  Where providers are just part of the daemon."
                },
                {
                    "file": "designs/cxl-cci-over-mctp.md",
                    "line": 81,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Patrick Williams",
                        "email": "patrick@stwcx.xyz",
                        "username": "williamspatrick"
                    },
                    "message": "Why?"
                },
                {
                    "file": "designs/cxl-cci-over-mctp.md",
                    "line": 104,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Patrick Williams",
                        "email": "patrick@stwcx.xyz",
                        "username": "williamspatrick"
                    },
                    "message": "Definitely need more examples here."
                },
                {
                    "file": "designs/cxl-cci-over-mctp.md",
                    "line": 115,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Patrick Williams",
                        "email": "patrick@stwcx.xyz",
                        "username": "williamspatrick"
                    },
                    "message": "Please point to this proposed dbus API.  I can't picture it from this sentence."
                },
                {
                    "file": "designs/cxl-cci-over-mctp.md",
                    "line": 118,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Patrick Williams",
                        "email": "patrick@stwcx.xyz",
                        "username": "williamspatrick"
                    },
                    "message": "Why would we be sending raw CCI messages?  We should not be exposing protocol details to the rest of the BMC.  Present these as dbus objects or listen to existing dbus objects (and react to signals from them) to initiate requests."
                },
                {
                    "file": "designs/cxl-cci-over-mctp.md",
                    "line": 122,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Patrick Williams",
                        "email": "patrick@stwcx.xyz",
                        "username": "williamspatrick"
                    },
                    "message": "Can you give a concrete example?  I don't know why we'd need to talk to a single remote device over multiple channels."
                },
                {
                    "file": "designs/cxl-cci-over-mctp.md",
                    "line": 129,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Patrick Williams",
                        "email": "patrick@stwcx.xyz",
                        "username": "williamspatrick"
                    },
                    "message": "Alternatives that should be discussed:\n\n- CCI as a shared library.\n- Added to an existing MCTP daemon.\n- Added to pldmd.\n- Added to libmctp (or libpldm)."
                },
                {
                    "file": "designs/cxl-cci-over-mctp.md",
                    "line": 133,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Patrick Williams",
                        "email": "patrick@stwcx.xyz",
                        "username": "williamspatrick"
                    },
                    "message": "Please fill in."
                },
                {
